This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the translation of 3D surface models to internal body structures using deep convolutional neural networks. It also involves image processing and analysis, which are common topics in computer vision. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Since the paper deals with medical imaging and the estimation of internal body structures, it is also likely to belong to the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of 3D models, which makes it possible to belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
